  "coaching_notes": "This user has a trained editorial eye for nonprofit writing clich\u00e9s and will reject them immediately\u2014phrases like 'your generous support,' 'making a difference,' or 'we want to show you' are treated as failures of craft, not acceptable defaults. They think architecturally: every section must serve the next, and endings must set up future asks without being transactional. When giving feedback, they often articulate the fix better than they realize\u2014listen for the rubric in their complaints, and mirror their own language back to them."
